HEADWORD: Horseflesh
<hw>Horse"flesh`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ocir⟧rs"fl⟦ecr⟧sh`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The flesh of horses.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> horsemeat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Chinese eat <qex>horseflesh</qex> at this day.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Horses, generally; the qualities of a horse; <as>as,
he is a judge of <ex>horseflesh</ex></as>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Horseflesh ore</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>a miner's
name for bornite, in allusion to its peculiar reddish color on fresh
facture.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horsefly</ent>⟦br⟧
